n\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:467:\"wpStoreCart 2.2.6 has been released. The admin product page has received a bit of a makeover, now including 3 tabs: 1. Product 2. Variations 3. View Page In this release, the big new feature is Advanced Variations. They are called Advanced Variations for a reason, they take some understand and skill in order to setup&#8230; <a class=\"continue_reading\" href=\"http://wpstorecart.com/wpstorecart-2-2-6-is-released-with-advanced-variations/\">Continue reading &#187;</a>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1528:\"<p>wpStoreCart 2.2.6 has been released.  The admin product page has received a bit of a makeover, now including 3 tabs:<br />\n1. Product<br />\n2. Variations<br />\n3. View Page</p>\n<p>In this release, the big new feature is Advanced Variations.  They are called Advanced Variations for a reason, they take some understand and skill in order to setup properly, and if setup improperly, have the potential to confuse you and customers.  To that end, we&#8217;re working on written documentation and video tutorials.  However, in the meantime, I suggest unless you&#8217;re looking for a challenge on your TEST website, then don&#8217;t use this until the documentation has been written.<br />\n<span id=\"more-629\"></span><br />\nIn a nutshell, Advanced Variations (which cannot be used with Simple Variations) allow you to force a customer to fill select one variation from each advanced variation category.  Each and every combination of all variations has it&#8217;s own price, which you must set individually in the admin panel for each possible combination.  Sounds confusing.  Well, it is, especially without any screenshots, without a glossary of the terms we&#8217;re using, without a working example for you to mess with.  See, that&#8217;s why I am saying, just wait for the written and video tutorials.  It won&#8217;t be long.</p>\n<p>In other news, 2.2.7 is coming out shortly, and it includes some coupon enhancements, including discount percentage (as in, you can create a coupon that takes 33% off a product, etc.)</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:83:\"http://wpstorecart.com/wpstorecart-2-2-6-is-released-with-advanced-variations/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n	\n	\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:43:\"wpStoreCart 2.2.6 Coming Out Later Tonight!\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"http://wpstorecart.com/wpstorecart-2-2-6-coming-out-later-tonight/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:75:\"http://wpstorecart.com/wpstorecart-2-2-6-coming-out-later-tonight/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 25 Apr 2011 22:39:01 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"http://wpstorecart.com/?p=621\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:490:\"Just a heads up that in the next release, 2.2.6, we&#8217;ve added &#8220;Advanced Variations&#8221; which are a way to have separate price and inventory for specific variations. The old variation system that has been present from 2.1.x up until 2.2.5 is also going to remain, but these variations are now called &#8220;Simple Variations.&#8221; One new&#8230; <a class=\"continue_reading\" href=\"http://wpstorecart.com/wpstorecart-2-2-6-coming-out-later-tonight/\">Continue reading &#187;</a>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:835:\"<p>Just a heads up that in the next release, 2.2.6, we&#8217;ve added &#8220;Advanced Variations&#8221; which are a way to have separate price and inventory for specific variations.  The old variation system that has been present from 2.1.x up until 2.2.5 is also going to remain, but these variations are now called &#8220;Simple Variations.&#8221;   One new feature of &#8220;Simple Variations&#8221; is that they can have a quantity as well.</p>\n<p>However, in wpStoreCart 2.2.6 inventory quantities as described above will not be available yet.  In 2.2.6 we have the introduction of the Advanced Variations, and in wpStoreCart 2.2.7 we will have the inclusion of stock control for all types of variations.</p>\n<p>Anyway, just wanted to give everyone a quick heads up that a new, improved wpStoreCart is about to be released.  </p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"http://wpstorecart.com/wpstorecart-2-2-6-coming-out-later-tonight/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n	\n	\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"wpStoreCart 2.2.5 Released\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:50:\"http://wpstorecart.com/wpstorecart-2-2-5-released/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"http://wpstorecart.com/wpstorecart-2-2-5-released/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sun, 24 Apr 2011 20:56:26 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"http://wpstorecart.com/?p=618\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:451:\"It took months of coding and testing, but wpStoreCart 2.2 was released last week. Since then, we&#8217;ve released 5 patches, some of which addressed issues with shipping, others which implemented features that we were trying to have out in version 2.2.0, such as guest checkout. Over the next several weeks, expect a flood of new&#8230; <a class=\"continue_reading\" href=\"http://wpstorecart.com/wpstorecart-2-2-5-released/\">Continue reading &#187;</a>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1080:\"<p>It took months of coding and testing, but wpStoreCart 2.2 was released last week.  Since then, we&#8217;ve released 5 patches, some of which addressed issues with shipping, others which implemented features that we were trying to have out in version 2.2.0, such as guest checkout.  Over the next several weeks, expect a flood of new releases.  For example, in our next release, we&#8217;re updating the variation system to allow much more versatility and features.  We&#8217;re also going to be wrapping up the wpStoreCart Theme and releasing it the WordPress theme database so that we can deliver updates to the theme without having to update the wpStoreCart plugin.  Also, we have our first premium WordPress theme nearing release, which is a theme geared for shops that sell t-shirts and other types of clothing (although you can sell anything with the theme, it has been designed to be an ideal clothing store.)  More updates as they happen.  Thanks for checking out wpStoreCart.  Let us know in the comments how wpStoreCart 2.2.x has been for you!</p>\n<p>NTPATDTYB3DJ</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:55:\"http://wpstorecart.com/wpstorecart-2-2-5-released/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n	\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n	\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"New Features Galore!  wpStoreCart 2.2 is Almost Here!\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:74:\"http://wpstorecart.com/new-features-galore-wpstorecart-2-2-is-almost-here/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:83:\"http://wpstorecart.com/new-features-galore-wpstorecart-2-2-is-almost-here/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sat, 02 Apr 2011 07:33:50 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"http://wpstorecart.com/?p=547\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:492:\"There has been so much work put into the latest version of wpStoreCart. I&#8217;ve literally tried to address everything that I could from the feedback I&#8217;ve received from our users. Here&#8217;s what has been accomplished on wpStoreCart 2.2 so far: Added the ability to make registration optional A long requested feature, in version 2.2 the&#8230; <a class=\"continue_reading\" href=\"http://wpstorecart.com/new-features-galore-wpstorecart-2-2-is-almost-here/\">Continue reading &#187;</a>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11391:\"<p>There has been so much work put into the latest version of wpStoreCart.  I&#8217;ve literally tried to address everything that I could from the feedback I&#8217;ve received from our users.  Here&#8217;s what has been accomplished on wpStoreCart 2.2 so far:<br />\n<span id=\"more-547\"></span></p>\n<h2>Added the ability to make registration optional</h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://wpstorecart.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/screenshot-1.png\"><img src=\"http://wpstorecart.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/screenshot-1-300x211.png\" alt=\"\" title=\"screenshot-1\" width=\"300\" height=\"211\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-555\" /></a><br />\nA long requested feature, in version 2.2 the bare minimum information needed to progress through checkout is an email address.  It is still highly recommended to require registration for shipping, taxes, and other legal reasons.</p>\n<h2>Added the ability to turn coupons on or off globally and to hide the coupon form when they are disabled</h2>\n<p><img src=\"http://wpstorecart.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/coupons.png\" alt=\"\" title=\"coupons\" width=\"323\" height=\"86\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-558\" /><br />\nAnother often requested feature has been the ability to disable to coupon system.  Here&#8217;s one spot to do it.  You can also do it from Settings > Display Settings > Checkout Page</p>\n<h2>Added the ability to create, edit, delete, and reorder optional and required profile fields for registration and/or checkout</h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://wpstorecart.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/screenshot-2.png\"><img src=\"http://wpstorecart.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/screenshot-2-300x223.png\" alt=\"\" title=\"screenshot-2\" width=\"300\" height=\"223\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-559\" /></a><br />\nHere was an essential feature that many people requested: the ability to prompt for additional information, such as shipping and billing addresses during checkout.  This is fully customizable and uses drag and drop and other Ajax goodies to make manging this new feature a breeze.  You can find this new feature in Settings > Customers</p>\n<h2>Added the &#8220;Setup Wizard&#8221;, a new, user friendly way to quickly and easily setup wpStoreCart</h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://wpstorecart.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/screenshot-1.jpg\"><img src=\"http://wpstorecart.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/screenshot-1-300x215.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"screenshot-1\" width=\"300\" height=\"215\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-560\" /></a><br />\nThe &#8220;Setup Wizard&#8221; is something I envisioned for wpStoreCart from the very start.  Basically, the goal with the wizard is to allow anyone, even non-technical users, to have a way to easily configure wpStoreCart.  The Setup Wizard goes through a series of questions and ask you what your store sells, how you take payment, what type of shipping options (if any) that your provide, and more.  It is accessible from all wpStoreCart admin screens.</p>\n<h2>Added UPS, FedEx, and USPS shipping options with calculations (disabled on digital only stores)</h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://wpstorecart.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/screenshot-3.png\"><img src=\"http://wpstorecart.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/screenshot-3-300x196.png\" alt=\"\" title=\"screenshot-3\" width=\"300\" height=\"196\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-561\" /></a><br />\nShipping has always been pretty dismal in wpStoreCart, but no longer.  We now offer a ton of shipping options, and the final version of 2.2 will offer even more shipping options than what is shown here.  </p>\n<h2>Added weight, length, width, and height attributes to products (disabled on digital only stores)</h2>\n<p>This information was definitely required for shipping calculations.  However, it is still optional information and for Digital Only stores, these fields are hidden.</p>\n<h2>Added shipping to the checkout information</h2>\n<p>You can optionally display shipping amounts in both the checkout widget and the checkout page.  This option is automatically set to disable shipping on Digital Only stores.</p>\n<h2>Added $devOptions[\'storetype\'] which configures the site for physical, digital, or mixed stores</h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://wpstorecart.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/screenshot-2.jpg\"><img src=\"http://wpstorecart.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/screenshot-2-300x223.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"screenshot-2\" width=\"300\" height=\"223\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-564\" /></a><br />\nYou&#8217;ve read about &#8220;Digital Only&#8221; stores here in this blog post, and here&#8217;s what I am talking about.  If you sell only digital products, such as mp3s or software, than things like shipping and product weight don&#8217;t make sense for your site.  With this new option, you can tell wpStoreCart that you either sell:</p>\n<ul>\n<ol>Both physical and digital items, so all product options are available (recommended)</ol>\n<ol>Only physical items are sold, so all digital file uploads are disabled and hidden, or</ol>\n<ol>Only digital items are sold, so all shipping and physical properties are hidden</ol>\n</ul>\n<h2>Added integration with the wpStoreCartTheme wordpress theme.</h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://wpstorecart.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/screenshot-3.jpg\"><img src=\"http://wpstorecart.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/screenshot-3-300x204.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"screenshot-3\" width=\"300\" height=\"204\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-565\" /></a><br />\nwpStoreCart 2.2 and above comes with it&#8217;s own high end, ajax enabled theme.  In fact, you can checkout a live demo of the theme and wpStoreCart 2.2 over at this URL: <a href=\"http://wpstorecart.com/demo/\">http://wpstorecart.com/demo/</a></p>\n<p>So not only does wpStoreCart 2.2 come with this amazing theme, but it is also completely integrated into the wpStoreCart administration panel.  You can edit the ajax slide show, adjust the header, turn on and off the ajax features, and more.</p>\n<p>There&#8217;s a bunch of other stuff, but in brief, here&#8217;s some of the other additions and changes in 2.2:</p>\n<ul>\n<li> Added Username, Password, Email, Total, Shipping, Login, Logout, My Orders and Purchases, Required Symbol, Required Symbol Description, and Register to the language menu</li>\n<li> Added the ability to display shipping, subtotal, and total in the checkout page and widget, configurable from the Display Settings admin page</li>\n<li> Started the process of adding phpDoc blocks to the source code of wpStoreCart, for better readability and 3rd party code additions</li>\n<li> Removed usage of WP_PLUGIN_URL and replaced with plugins_url() to help make wpStoreCart more SSL friendly (front end only, admin not finished)</li>\n<li> Changes the logo to wpStoreCart PRO when PRO is installed, changed most admin images</li>\n<li> Disables the WordPress 3.1 admin bar for users who are not administrators, for compatibilities sake</li>\n<li>Reorganized the Display Settings admin page</li>\n<li> Loads the WordPress core file pluggable.php to insure compatibility</li>\n<li> Fixed default value missing for PayPal active</li>\n<li> Fixed a bug with Authorize.NET and 2CheckOut not getting the right price for multiple items</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>That&#8217;s great and everything, but when will it be released?</h2>\n<p>We are trying to get wpStoreCart 2.2 done as soon as possible, but there&#8217;s still a lot to be down.  In fact, here&#8217;s exactly what&#8217;s left to be done.  When all these tasks are finished and the beta testers get done with it, then we will release it&#8230; but not until then.  Here&#8217;s that list:</p>\n<p><strong>Wizard Issues</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li> &#8211; Initial wpStoreCart error needs to point to wizard</li>\n<li> &#8211; If the wizard has never been run, it should run for new installs and upgrades alike.</li>\n<li> &#8211; If store is mixed or physical, then shipping is enabled. There should be a few screens to help setup shipping in this case</li>\n<li> &#8211; User registration should be addressed in the wizard as well</li>\n<li> &#8211; Menu should be updated so that the different sections of the wizard (general, payment gateways, shipping, and registration) are easily visited without going through the whole wizard</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Registration &#038; Checkout Issues</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li> &#8211; Make required registration fields actually be required</li>\n<li> &#8211; Fix ugly CSS issues for non-wpsc themes</li>\n<li> &#8211; Fix the registration process so that it works with the new system</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Shipping Issues</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li> &#8211; Add flat rate shipping, with five options: 1) Use a Flat Rate for all products, each item in the cart occurs an additional shipping fee of the specified amount.  2) Use individual Flate Rates specified for each product. 3) Use one Flat rate for the entire shopping cart, regardless of the number of items in the cart. 4) Disable Flat Rate shipping 5) The amount of the flat rate if option 1 or 3 is chosen</li>\n<li> &#8211; For each shipping option (USP, USPS, FedEx, Flat rate, etc) that is enabled, put a checkbox to allow it to be used on each specific product. During checkout, all products would be checked to see if they allowed all shipping options.  If one item didn&#8217;t allow a specific shipping type, then it will disable that shipping type for the entire order.</li>\n<li> &#8211; During checkout, if flat rate shipping is On and all products in the cart qualify to use it, then it will display the subtotal using flat rate shipping by default, and present an interface to change shipping to another applicable shipping option if one is available</li>\n<li> &#8211; If shipping must be calculated, then instead of numbers being listed for subtotal, it will be replaced by an interface to access the available and applicable shipping options for the current cart</li>\n<li> &#8211; Shipping interface needs to be built that prompts for and saves the user&#8217;s zipcode</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Import/Export Issue</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li> &#8211; This feature will be delayed once again</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Taxes &#038; Other Fees</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li> &#8211; Add Taxes &#038; Other Fees to the Payment Settings page</li>\n<li> &#8211; Taxes/Fees can be tied to either Countries as global fees, or States as global fees</li>\n<li> &#8211; Each tax/fee can either be a flat fee, a percentage of the total of the cart without shipping, or a percentage of the total of the cart WITH shipping</li>\n</ul>\n<p> <strong>Theme Issues</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li> &#8211; Slide show admin side needs the ability to add and remove a href tags</li>\n<li> &#8211; Product sidebar needs to be addressed in both wpStoreCart Theme and Plugin</li>\n<li> &#8211; Default sidebar needs to be coded</li>\n<li> &#8211; Demo mode needs to be coded (demo mode shows off the theme as a full ecommerce site, without the actual use of need for wpStoreCart.)</li>\n<li> &#8211; Theme needs to attempt to install wpStoreCart plugin if it&#8217;s not found, and run in demo mode if wpStoreCart is not available after attempt</li>\n<li> &#8211; When wpStoreCart Theme is finished, it needs to be included with Plugin and automatically installed.  If install fails, error should alert user</li>\n<li> &#8211; Since wpStoreCart Plugin also contains the theme files, it should alert admin via error message if the theme was modified at all, and inform them that child themes is the way to go, etc.</li>\n</ul>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:79:\"http://wpstorecart.com/new-features-galore-wpstorecart-2-2-is-almost-here/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:29:\"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/\";a:2:{s:9:\"thumbnail\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:3:\"url\";s:74:\"http://wpstorecart.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/screenshot-1