fected sites that have upgraded to 3.8.7.3. Again we&#8217;re terribly sorry about this mistake and promise to be more careful in future releases.</p>\n<p>Second, the last blog announcement for 3.8.7.3 raised <a href=\"http://getshopped.org/uncategorized/wp-e-commerce-3-8-7-3-security-release/#comment-8644\">some discussion</a> about the way our release announcements should be improved. Thank you for your feedback. We are working on creating a newsletter so that you will receive release announcements directly to your mail box.</p>\n<p>We also realized that saying &#8220;it&#8217;s a security update&#8221; without disclosing any information sort of defeated the purpose of the announcement, and we&#8217;re sorry for that. So here it goes:</p>\n<p>The latest upgrade include fixes for a few potential security issues. These issues affect both 3.7.x and 3.8.x sites. It is <strong>critical that you upgrade your site.</strong></p>\n<p>For sites currently running 3.8.x, you can confidently upgrade your site to 3.8.7.4. You can do that by using automatic update in WordPress, or by <a href=\"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/wp-e-commerce/\">downloading it from wordpress.org</a>.</p>\n<p>For sites running 3.7.x, <strong>DO NOT</strong> upgrade using WordPress built-in automatic upgrade. Please go to the <a href=\"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/wp-e-commerce/download/\">Other Version section of our plugin page on wordpress.org</a>, and download 3.7.8.2. Then extract it and upload that version to your wp-content/plugins folder. However, note that we no longer officially support 3.7.x sites. <strong>Active development for bug fixes and new features for 3.7.x has stopped. It&#8217;s highly recommended that the latest 3.8.x version is used to run your shops.</strong></p>\n<p>We can&#8217;t stress this enough: <strong>before upgrading, make sure you have a back up of your files and database, just in case</strong>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\