:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1608:\"<p>Hi everyone,</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s been a week since our <a href=\"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-7-beta/\">beta releases of 3.8.7</a>. Since then we have resolved several important bugs introduced in the beta release, and we&#8217;re happy to announce the first release candidate of 3.8.7. By now, we&#8217;re confident to say 3.8.7-RC1 (short for release candidate 1) is stable enough for more widespread testing.</p>\n<p>There are two important issues that are resolved in the release candidate:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Stock clearance does not run as scheduled (introduced in beta release)</li>\n<li>Fancy notification not working (introduced in beta release)</li>\n<li>Category title is replaced by first product&#8217;s title, causing problems with themes that have a <em>while have_posts()</em> loop in page.php template</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span style=\"color: #cc3333;\"><strong>Attention</strong>:</span> Release Candidate means the software is relatively stable, but still not ready for production. Please make sure you&#8217;re only using it in a development or testing environment.</p>\n<p>If there&#8217;s no other issues discovered in the release candidate, the official release will be ready in no more than a week.</p>\n<p>As usual, if you find any issues in this release candidate, <a href=\"http://getshopped.org/forums/forum/alpha-beta-release-candidates/3-8-7-rc/\">there&#8217;s a forum where you can report</a>.</p>\n<div>\n<p>» <strong><a href=\"http://wp-e-commerce.googlecode.com/files/wp-e-commerce-3.8.7-rc1.zip\">Click here to download WP e-Commerce 3.8.7-RC1!</a></strong></p>\n</div>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:67:\"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/