onâ€™t just push our tofu agendas- we actually are real health care professionals. Donn Kropp founded the company in 2009 out of a desire to bring others to greater levels of health and wellness. With over ten years of emergency and trauma room experience Donn brings a seasoned, yet fresh approach.Â  Cogent means to make something lucid, coherent and easily understandable-We also inject a healthy dose of fun and humor into our business and products. Enough about us, we want our business to be about you! We want you to learn and have fun while you are doing it so that you can give the people you service the highest quality care possible.\r\n\r\n\r\nAbout Our Founder/Executive Director/Instructor:\r\n\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://clickceu.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/kropp_donn-about.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-199 alignright\" title=\"Donn Kropp, Founder of Cogent CEUs\" src=\"http://clickceu.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/kropp_donn-about.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"175\" height=\"183\" /></a>\r\n\r\nDonn Kropp\r\n\r\n\r\nAcademic Stuff: Bachelors of Science in Nursing 2001 from University of North Carolina- Charlotte\r\n\r\nWork Experience Stuff: ER/Trauma Nurse, Medical Consultant\r\n\r\nStuff He Likes to Do: Travel, read, anything death defying, golf, exercise, eat\r\n\r\nPlaces Heâ€™s Lived: Japan, North Carolina, California\r\n\r\nPlaces Heâ€™s Visited: Japan, Saipan, Belize, Ecuador, Costa Rica, Korea, India, Haiti, Germany, Czech Republic, Austria, Mexico\r\n\r\nPlaces He Wants To Visit: New Zealand, Australia, Iceland, Kansas\r\n\r\nEmbarrassing Moment: â€œAbout thirty seconds before giving a speech I spilled water in my lap from a water bottle. There was no podium to hide behind so I just started the speech out by saying I was just diagnosed with early onset urinary incontinence. It took about ten minutes to dry and it was quite embarrassing. Note to self- no water before giving a speech.â€\r\n\r\nIf you had a robot what would you train it to do? Give me daily deep tissue shiatsu massages.','About','','inherit','closed','closed','','2-revision-4','','','2011-08-23 18:55:00','2011-08-23 18:55:00','',2,'http://clickceu.com/2011/08/2-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(223,1,'2011-08-23 05:16:48','2011-08-23 05:16:48','Have you heard of MRSA? If you havenâ€™t you should. Your life or someone elseâ€™s may depend on it. M.R.S.A stands for Methicillin Resistant Staphylococcus Aureus, commonly referred to as â€œMERSAâ€ or just â€œStaph Infectionâ€. This course will help youÂ  understand MRSA so that you can institute safe and effective practices that will benefit yourself and the individuals you serve.\r\n\r\nMRSA has had a relatively short existence. It was first noticed in nursing homes and hospitals in the early 1960â€˜s. Until the mid-20th century, infectious diseases were the leading cause of death.Thanks to our good friend Alexander Flemingâ€™s accidental discovery of penicillin in 1928, there was a huge decrease in the incidences of diseases caused by bacteria.Â  Flemingâ€™s discovery took a little while to gain traction but when it did in the early 1940â€™s, this started the era of the â€œAntibiotic Phenomenonâ€. Antibiotics were hailed as miracle drugs. Previously untreatable conditions could now be overcome with a simple pill.Â  Unfortunately this isnâ€™t a happily-ever-after story.\r\n\r\nJust a decade later a resistant strain of Staphylococcus Aureus emerged. It was resistant not only to penicillin, but to newer antibiotics that were being developed such as: erythromycin, streptomycin, and tetracycline. A very costly lesson was being learned at this point; that lesson was, â€œBacteria have the ability to mutate.â€ Learn more about this superbug as seasoned registered nurse, Donn Kropp, demystifies this scourge.\r\n\r\n<strong>Course Objectives</strong>\r\nUpon completion of this course you will be able to:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Understand bacteria and their significance</li>\r\n	<li>Differentiate between Staphyloco