essment skills, a firm knowledge base, and a well thought out action plan these diseases can be prevented and/or effectively managed. Educating yourself and spreading knowledge to others will move society to greater and greater levels of health and wellness. Take care of your lungs, love your lungs. You only have two of them and you only have one life.\r\n\r\n<strong>Course Objectives</strong>\r\nUpon completion of this course you will be able to:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Understand and implement the components of a basic respiratory assessment.</li>\r\n	<li>Identify common signs and symptoms of respiratory distress.</li>\r\n	<li>Define the causes, signs and symptoms of asthma, pneumonia and COPD.</li>\r\n	<li>Understand the management and prevention of asthma, pneumonia and COPD.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Chapter Content</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Introduction</li>\r\n	<li>Objectives</li>\r\n	<li>Respiratory Review</li>\r\n	<li>Identifying Respiratory Problems</li>\r\n	<li>Asthma</li>\r\n	<li>Pneumonia</li>\r\n	<li>COPD</li>\r\n	<li>Conclusion</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>Course Approvals</strong>: This course is pending approval by the following boards\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>NAB: This educational offering has been reviewed by the National Continuing Education Review Service (NCERS) of the National Association of Boards of Examiners of Long Term Care Administrators (NAB).</li>\r\n	<li>California Adult Residential Facility (ARF) Vendor No. 2000149-735-2 Course Approval No. ____________</li>\r\n	<li>Residential Care Facility for the Elderly (RCFE) Vendor No. 2000149-740-2 Course Approval No._________</li>\r\n	<li>Group Home (GH) Vendor No. 2000149-730-2Â Course Approval No. __________</li>\r\n	<li>CA &amp; FL Board of Registered Nursing: CA Provider No.__________Â FL Provider No.________</li>\r\n	<li>California Board of Vocational Nursing Provider No.___________</li>\r\n	<li>Psychiatric Technicians Provider No. ___________</li>\r\n	<li>CA Department of Health Services, Aid &amp; Technician